2017 WW49-WW50 NFVi Silver Release Announcement (BKC #23)

\n \n \n \n

DEG Platform Integration Team

\n \n
\n\n \n

The DEG platform Integration team announces the release of 2017 WW49-WW50 NFVi Silver release package for Intel internal use. The release is based on OS of\n \n RHEL7.3/\n \n Ubuntu14.04.5/\n \n Ubuntu16.04.1\n server. The auto-installer packages are available in the Artifactory server (both SH site and OR site). Any questions please contact Wang, Alex.\n

Key Update

  • Total test cases: 50; Attempted test cases: 50 (Attempted rate:100%);\nPassed test cases: 50 and pass rate is 100.00%
  • In this cycle of validation, the primary OS\ncoverage is on RHEL7.3, the release packages are built for all 3\ndifferent OSes

  • Updated DPDK to 17.11
  • Updated SPDK to 17.10.1
  • Platform Service Assurance - libvirt (v2.0.0) collectd\ntest coverage addition from this cycle
  • Configuration/validation OS mapping, more details please refer to the HW configuration
    • System A: WFT + Niantic10G + Lewis Hill QAT, validate on Ubuntu16.04.1 and Ubuntu14.04.5
    • System A+: WFT + FVL25G, validate on Ubuntu14.04.5
    • System B: WFQ + FVL25G + NVMe P3600, validate on RHE7.3 or Ubuntu16.04.1, do validation on one every 2 week, then alternate
\n \n


Release Note

\xc2\xb7       \nUbuntu14.04.5 is releases\nwith kernel 3.13.0-100 generic, only contain the SW package, no auto-installer\nsupport, semi-auto installation step as below:

\xc2\xa7 \nInstall Ubuntu14.04.5 Server

\xc2\xa7 \nDownload the SW package and unzip it, Copy the APP folder to\n/opt/ of target SUT

\xc2\xa7 \nNavigate to /opt/APP/script, run update_kernel.sh to update\nkernel to 3.13.0-100, reboot the system 

\xc2\xa7 \nNavigate to /opt/APP/script, run setup.sh to install required\nlibs and SW dependencies

\xc2\xa7 \nNote: All SW\ningredients are installed after running /opt/APP/script/setup.sh

\xc2\xb7       \nUbuntu16.04.1/RHEL7.3 are released as\nauto-installer, refer to Auto-Installation Guide for installation details

\xc2\xb7       \nPlease refer to README for the WAR details of following 2 issues:

WAR\nfor "watchdog\nerror when install Ubuntu OS after flash BMC from 0.71.d8978c76"\n has been applied into BKC since BKC #10
